        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. If you only operate within Georgia, you register under the Georgia Intrastate Motor Carrier (GIMC) program through the Georgia Department of Public Safety. You'll need a USDOT number with a 'GA' suffix displayed on your vehicle. If you ever cross state lines, you'll need federal MC authority instead."
        }
